        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 9:16PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 916 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Seven Rivers Airport, or 10 miles southwest of
Artesia, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Artesia, Atoka, Dayton, and Artesia Municipal Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
